Therefore, I recommend the test from the age of 50 or 40 years, respectively, if you have a direct relative who already had prostate cancer.
There is also a higher risk in African-American men.
The most important thing is to make the right decision once a cancer has been detected.
There are cancers that are aggressive and others that are indolent.
