This judgment is not currently being implemented.
It is a problem between a South American and a Central American state.
Conflicts are inevitable, but they must be overcome in the pursuit of a common path.
They need to be comprehensively treated so that you can overcome them and look forward.
He also relied on a good conclusion of the disputes over the maritime borders between Peru and Chile before the same court, saying that "it is right for Latin America to call on international authorities if both countries commit to accept the verdict, even if it is very hard."
Regarding the possibility that he will stand as a candidate for the next presidential election in Ecuador to achieve his third consecutive mandate, he said that he sees this opportunity “with a lot of optimism and joy, although sometimes it is very difficult.”
