Power never interested me personally, but under circumstances as unfair as in Ecuador, this socio-economic poverty can only be corrected by political power.
“My political movement had the belief that it was me who guaranteed this likely victory, so I have to fulfill that responsibility,” he said.
If I were to win, it would be my last period as president, after which I withdraw from public life.
This also applies if we lose.
“That’s decided,” he said.
Correa also referred to the treatment of the health problems of the President of Venezuela, Hugo Chávez, in Cuba.
I just spoke with Vice-President Nicolás Maduro of Venezuela, who told me that he had traveled there for a planned, routine treatment and that he was expected to be able to travel back to Cuba after the election campaign.
