Héctor "Hetin" Reyes: "Basketball was my life"
The basketball world champion, Héctor "Hetin" Reyes, has been involved in basketball for more than 60 years and has travelled the world.
Few in Puerto Rico have such a large intellectual collection of the country's history of basketball as Héctor "Hetin" Reyes.
Before being tied to a wheelchair by a stroke in 2008, Rexes was part of this sport for 6 years, whether as a lower class player, first national league player, authorized representative and leader in the BSN with the Vaqueros de Bayamón or president of the basketball association.
